:17:10'),(220,'wildpage',176,'{\"WildPage\":{\"title\":\"Portfolio\",\"content\":\"<h2>Portfolio<\\/h2>\\n<p>My specialization is <em>PHP <\\/em>&amp;<em> MySQL<\\/em> application development. I love creating semantic <em>(X)HTML\\/CSS<\\/em> templates and have solid background in <em>web graphics<\\/em>. I work a lot with <em>Javascript<\\/em> and various AJAX implementations.<\\/p>\\n<h3>Wildflower CMS<\\/h3>\\n<p><a title=\\\"files-manager.jpg\\\" rel=\\\"lightbox\\\" href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.klevo.sk\\/uploads\\/files-manager.jpg\\\"><img src=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.klevo.sk\\/uploads\\/files-manager.thumbnail.jpg\\\" alt=\\\"files-manager.jpg\\\" \\/><\\/a> <a title=\\\"page-edit.jpg\\\" rel=\\\"lightbox\\\" href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.klevo.sk\\/uploads\\/page-edit.jpg\\\"><img src=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.klevo.sk\\/uploads\\/page-edit.thumbnail.jpg\\\" alt=\\\"page-edit.jpg\\\" \\/><\\/a><\\/p>\\n<p><strong>Description<\\/strong>: I&rsquo;ve build this content management system and application platform to ease and enhance the process I build websites. The biggest asset is the user and developer friendly oriented design of the whole system. And it&rsquo;s open source.<\\/p>\\n<p><strong>Link<\\/strong>: <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/wf.klevo.sk\\/\\\">wf.klevo.sk<\\/a><\\/p>\\n<h3>Orkney Crofts<\\/h3>\\n<p><a title=\\\"orkney_home_resize.png\\\" rel=\\\"lightbox\\\" href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.klevo.sk\\/uploads\\/orkney_home_resize.png\\\"><img src=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.klevo.sk\\/uploads\\/orkney_home_resize.thumbnail.png\\\" alt=\\\"orkney_home_resize.png\\\" \\/><\\/a> <a title=\\\"orkney-booking.png\\\" rel=\\\"lightbox\\\" href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.klevo.sk\\/uploads\\/orkney-booking.png\\\"><img src=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.klevo.sk\\/uploads\\/orkney-booking.thumbnail.png\\\" alt=\\\"orkney-booking.png\\\" \\/><\\/a><\\/p>\\n<p><strong>Description<\\/strong>: Site presenting a luxurious accommodation at Orkney islands. Contains a booking system. It&rsquo;s build on my new CakePHP CMS - <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/wf.klevo.sk\\/\\\">Wildflower<\\/a>.<\\/p>\\n<p><strong>Link<\\/strong>: <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.orkneycrofts.com\\/\\\">www.orkneycrofts.com<\\/a><\\/p>\\n<h3>Chatbox<\\/h3>\\n<p><a title=\\\"Chatbox customize page\\\" rel=\\\"lightbox\\\" href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.klevo.sk\\/uploads\\/chatcreator1.jpg\\\"><img src=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.klevo.sk\\/uploads\\/chatcreator1.thumbnail.jpg\\\" alt=\\\"Chatbox customize page\\\" \\/><\\/a> <a title=\\\"Chatbox done page\\\" rel=\\\"lightbox\\\" href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.klevo.sk\\/uploads\\/chatcreator2.jpg\\\"><img src=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.klevo.sk\\/uploads\\/chatcreator2.thumbnail.jpg\\\" alt=\\\"Chatbox done page\\\" \\/><\\/a><\\/p>\\n<p><strong>Description<\\/strong>: Chat application that can be embeded in any web page. Build on <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/cakephp.org\\/\\\">CakePHP<\\/a> and <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/jquery.com\\/\\\">JQuery<\\/a>. This project no longer exists. I&rsquo;ll probably release the code under some open source license.<\\/p>\"}}',5,'2009-01-14 10:14:03'),(221,'wildpage',176,'{\"WildPage\":{\"description_meta_tag\":\"\"}}',6,'2009-01-14 10:14:19'),(222,'wildpost',46,'{\"WildPost\":[]}',5,'2009-01-14 16:21:39'),(223,'wildpage',185,'{\"WildPage\":{\"title\":\"New home page\"}}',1,'2009-01-14 16:25:39'),(224,'wildpage',185,'{\"WildPage\":{\"title\":\"New home page\",\"content\":\"<p>Home content.<\\/p>\"}}',2,'2009-01-14 16:25:48'),(225,'wildpost',47,'{\"WildPost\":[]}',1,'2009-01-14 22:00:34'),(226,'wildpage',186,'{\"WildPage\":{\"title\":\"New articles for 2009\"}}',1,'2009-01-14 22:13:41'),(227,'wildpage',186,'{\"WildPage\":{\"title\":\"New articles for 2009\",\"content\":\"<p>I won\'t to write about..<\\/p>\\n<p>This is a really cool editor.<\\/p>\"}}',2,'2009-01-14 22:14:02'),(228,'wildpage',179,'{\"WildPage\":{\"title\":\"Model tweaks\",\"content\":\"<p><img src=\\\"\\/wildflower\\/uploads\\/company-image.jpg\\\" alt=\\\"company-image.jpg\\\" \\/>. Wicked.<\\/p>\"}}',2,'2009-01-19 04:30:00'),(229,'wildpage',187,'{\"WildPage\":{\"title\":\"\"}}',1,'2009-01-19 04:36:55'),(230,'wildpage',188,'{\"WildPage\":{\"title\":\"@todo: Empty title pages support\"}}',1,'2009-01-19 04:37:52'),(231,'wildpost',48,'{\"WildPost\":[]}',1,'2009-01-19 04:44:44'),(232,'wildpage',189,'{\"WildPage\":{\"title\":\"Documentation\"}}',1,'2009-01-19 04:57:28'),(233,'wildpage',189,'{\"WildPage\":{\"title\":\"Documentation\",\"content\":\"\"}}',2,'2009-01-19 04:57:33'),(234,'wildpage',190,'{\"WildPage\":{\"title\":\"Feature tour\"}}',1,'2009-01-19 05:03:37'),(235,'wildpage',185,'{\"WildPage\":{\"title\":\"Home page\",\"content\":\"<div class=\\\"summary\\\">\\n<p>You can take advantage of themes, making it easy to switch the look and feel of your page quickly and easily.<\\/p>\\n<p>To use themes, you need to tell your controller to use the ThemeView class instead of the default View class.<\\/p>\\n<a class=\\\"codeToggle\\\" href=\\\"http:\\/\\/book.cakephp.org\\/view\\/488\\/Themes#\\\">Plain Text View<\\/a>\\n<pre class=\\\"code\\\">class ExampleController extends AppController {<br \\/>    var $view = \'Theme\';<br \\/>}<br \\/><\\/pre>\\n<ol class=\\\"code\\\">\\n<li><code><span class=\\\"keyword\\\">class <\\/span><span class=\\\"default\\\">ExampleController <\\/span><span class=\\\"keyword\\\">extends <\\/span><span class=\\\"default\\\">AppController <\\/span><span class=\\\"keyword\\\">{<\\/span><\\/code><\\/li>\\n<li class=\\\"even\\\"><code><span class=\\\"keyword\\\"> var <\\/span><span class=\\\"default\\\">$view <\\/span><span class=\\\"keyword\\\">= <\\/span><span class=\\\"string\\\">\'Theme\'<\\/span><span class=\\\"keyword\\\">;<\\/span><\\/code><\\/li>\\n<li><code><span class=\\\"keyword\\\">}<\\/span><\\/code><\\/li>\\n<\\/ol>\\n<p>To declare which theme to use by default, specify the theme name in your controller.<\\/p>\\n<a class=\\\"codeToggle\\\" href=\\\"http:\\/\\/book.cakephp.org\\/view\\/488\\/Themes#\\\">Plain Text View<\\/a>\\n<pre class=\\\"code\\\">class ExampleController extends AppController {<br \\/>    var $view = \'Theme\';<br \\/>    var $theme = \'example\';<br \\/>}<br \\/><\\/pre>\\n<ol class=\\\"code\\\">\\n<li><code><span class=\\\"keyword\\\">class <\\/span><span class=\\\"default\\\">ExampleController <\\/span><span class=\\\"keyword\\\">extends <\\/span><span class=\\\"default\\\">AppController <\\/span><span class=\\\"keyword\\\">{<\\/span><\\/code><\\/li>\\n<li class=\\\"even\\\"><code><span class=\\\"keyword\\\"> var <\\/span><span class=\\\"default\\\">$view <\\/span><span class=\\\"keyword\\\">= <\\/span><span class=\\\"string\\\">\'Theme\'<\\/span><span class=\\\"keyword\\\">;<\\/span><\\/code><\\/li>\\n<li><code><span class=\\\"keyword\\\"> var <\\/span><span class=\\\"default\\\">$theme <\\/span><span class=\\\"keyword\\\">= <\\/span><span class=\\\"string\\\">\'example\'<\\/span><span class=\\\"keyword\\\">;<\\/span><\\/code><\\/li>\\n<li class=\\\"even\\\"><code><span class=\\\"keyword\\\">}<\\/span><\\/code><\\/li>\\n<\\/ol>\\n<p>You can also set or change the theme name within an action or within the <code>beforeFilter<\\/code> or <code>beforeRender<\\/code> callback functions.<\\/p>\\n<a class=\\\"codeToggle\\\" href=\\\"http:\\/\\/book.cakephp.org\\/view\\/488\\/Themes#\\\">Plain Text View<\\/a>\\n<pre class=\\\"code\\\">$this-&gt;theme = \'another_example\';<br \\/><\\/pre>\\n<ol class=\\\"code\\\">\\n<li><code><span class=\\\"default\\\">$this<\\/span><span class=\\\"keyword\\\">-&gt;<\\/span><span class=\\\"default\\\">theme <\\/span><span class=\\\"keyword\\\">= <\\/span><span class=\\\"string\\\">\'another_example\'<\\/span><span class=\\\"keyword\\\">;<\\/span><\\/code><\\/li>\\n<\\/ol>\\n<p>Theme view files need to be within the \\/app\\/views\\/themed\\/ folder. Within the themed folder, create a folder using the same name as your theme name. Beyond that, the folder structure within the \\/app\\/views\\/themed\\/example\\/ folder is exactly the same as \\/app\\/views\\/.<\\/p>\\n<p>For example, the view file for an edit action of a Posts controller would reside at \\/app\\/views\\/themed\\/example\\/posts\\/edit.ctp. Layout files would reside in \\/app\\/views\\/themed\\/example\\/layouts\\/.<\\/p>\\n<p>If a view file can\'t be found in the theme, CakePHP will try to locate the view file in the \\/app\\/views\\/ folder. This way, you can create master view files and simply override them on a case-by-case basis within your theme folder.<\\/p>\\n<p>If you have CSS or JavaScript files that are specific to your theme, you can store them in a themed folder within webroot. For example, your stylesheets would be stored in \\/app\\/webroot\\/themed\\/example\\/css\\/ and your JavaScript files would be stored in \\/app\\/webroot\\/themed\\/example\\/js\\/.<\\/p>\\n<p>All of CakePHP\'s built-in helpers are aware of themes and will create the correct paths automatically. Like view files, if a file isn\'t in the theme folder, it\'ll default to the main webroot folder.<\\/p>\\n<\\/div>\"}}',3,'2009-01-19 05:12:53');
